Flames shot from Thassalin's throat as the gigantic Thracian set a particular forest glade into play and then circled above it to detect any movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him ceased as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What is this, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thracian once!"
"If I'm flying myself, it's completely different from suddenly being lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"So bad was it really not, or, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly did not share Nyssis's opinion. He appeared less black than usual, and his claws had dug so deep into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. However, Thassalin seemed not to mind this at all. Nevertheless, he had realized that he had frightened his new friends and landed on an open clearing.
"sorry, but I smelled something. I had to take care of it!"
"But did you have to drag us along as well?" growled Tenuk as he climbed off Thassaline's back and slid down its tail. "And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong warrior has been left behind! How will he possibly catch up with us?"
"He will come up with something eventually..." grumbled Nyssi. "Retvik might not be the quickest, but he's not dumb."
"Okay, but can Retvik drive?"
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Do you think Retvik has ever driven a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I haven't seen him drive any fancy little car like Kayel's either. Besides, he only started taking the car for work because you always drive us around. He only has his bicycle."
Raucous laughter interrupted her. Thassalin seemed suddenly to find something incredibly funny, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"SORRY BUT I HAD TO PRESENT YOUR GIANT FRIEND IN ARMOR ON SUCH A TINY BICYCLE FOR TEMTHAN-KIDS. THAT WAS PRICELESS! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. WHAT A FANTASTIC IDEA! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, for he could imagine what was going on in Thassalin's head. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, picked something up and disappeared. When he returned after a short time, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, golden-white dragon creature. But its head was missing. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR YOUR SHREWS. I SMELL YOUR BLOOD. SOMETHING PUSHS ME TO PROTECT AND CHASE. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY NEAR."
The mighty Thraki suddenly turned stiff. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and hissed. Whatever it was, it spread out two enormous wing pairs and shot towards Thassalin, paying no mind to the three smaller beings in between them. Kayel and Tenuk managed to dive for cover just in time, but Nyssi was dragged along and nearly thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing him onto his back with his incredibly long and dexterous tail before swinging himself into the air. The black, dual-winged creature followed them at high speed.
Kayel snorted irritably as he took his rifle off his back and opened a bag that contained a ammunition belt. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thracian, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"You want to follow her?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... One of them is a huge monster!"
"Sure and what? I'm standing here with a high-caliber rifle in my hand and could start shooting right now. But, well, you know what – I would have to be able to see it in order to hit it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more space. With a soft, painful wheezing sound, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He rapidly changed into a normal, light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
The translation of "Steig auf." from German to English is "Mount up." or "Get on." depending on the context.
Like a normally appearing Thracian, Tenuk now had a proper scaled shield running along his back. Conveniently for Kayel, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, allowing him to hold on. It took Tenuk a little too long to get airborne, but once in the air, he oriented himself quickly and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized that they were not alone. A second dark creature shot upwards beneath them, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid a collision.
"This must be the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel frowned. He tried to shoot at the second beast but missed and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too preoccupied with focusing on the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, even though the other beast was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in his sights. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as he could aim and shoot more easily. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast, causing it to howl in pain and sink back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still pursuing them, but it definitely wouldn't be able to keep up with them.
A good distance in front of them, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin swung around, spitting flames at the scorched monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old trusty shotgun. Although it wasn't perhaps the first choice, maybe the shot would deter the black beast.
